You are building Phase 0 of the Yuni dating app. Read CLAUDE.md for full project context.

Create the project scaffolding for all three components. Do NOT implement any business logic yet — just the skeleton.

## Backend Setup

1. Create `backend/requirements.txt`:
```
fastapi==0.115.0
uvicorn[standard]==0.30.0
sqlalchemy[asyncio]==2.0.35
alembic==1.13.0
asyncpg==0.30.0
pydantic==2.9.0
pydantic-settings==2.5.0
python-jose[cryptography]==3.3.0
passlib[bcrypt]==1.7.4
python-multipart==0.0.9
websockets==13.0
httpx==0.27.0
pytest==8.3.0
pytest-asyncio==0.24.0
```

2. Create `backend/app/__init__.py` (empty)
3. Create `backend/app/main.py` with a minimal FastAPI app:
   - Title: "Yuni API"
   - CORS middleware allowing all origins (dev only)
   - A single `GET /api/health` endpoint returning `{"status": "ok"}`
4. Create `backend/app/config.py`:
   - Use pydantic-settings `BaseSettings` class
   - Fields: DATABASE_URL, DATABASE_TEST_URL, SECRET_KEY, ALGORITHM (default "HS256"), ACCESS_TOKEN_EXPIRE_MINUTES (default 1440)
   - `model_config = SettingsConfigDict(env_file=".env")`

## Mobile Setup

1. Initialize an Expo project in `mobile/`:
   - Create `mobile/package.json` with dependencies: expo (^52.0.0), react, react-native, typescript, @types/react, @react-navigation/native, @react-navigation/native-stack, @react-navigation/bottom-tabs, react-native-screens, react-native-safe-area-context, axios, @react-native-async-storage/async-storage
   - Dev dependencies: jest, @testing-library/react-native, @types/jest, react-test-renderer, typescript
2. Create `mobile/tsconfig.json` with strict TypeScript config extending expo's base
3. Create `mobile/app.json` with name "Yuni", slug "yuni"
4. Create `mobile/App.tsx` — minimal component that renders a Text element saying "Yuni"
5. Create `mobile/src/types/index.ts` — empty file with a comment "// TypeScript interfaces will be added here"
6. Create `mobile/jest.config.js` with preset "jest-expo" or a basic react-native jest config

## Dashboard Setup

1. Create `dashboard/package.json` with dependencies: next (^15.0.0), react (^19.0.0), react-dom (^19.0.0), typescript, @types/react, @types/node, tailwindcss (^4.0.0), @tailwindcss/postcss
   - Dev dependencies: jest, @testing-library/react, @testing-library/jest-dom, @types/jest, ts-jest
2. Create `dashboard/tsconfig.json` extending Next.js defaults
3. Create `dashboard/next.config.ts` — minimal Next.js config
4. Create `dashboard/postcss.config.mjs` with tailwindcss plugin
5. Create `dashboard/src/app/layout.tsx` — root layout with html/body, import globals.css
6. Create `dashboard/src/app/globals.css` — just `@import "tailwindcss";`
7. Create `dashboard/src/app/page.tsx` — simple page saying "Yuni Admin Dashboard"
8. Create `dashboard/jest.config.ts` with ts-jest preset for Next.js

IMPORTANT:
- Do NOT install dependencies — build.sh handles that
- Do NOT run any commands — just create the files
- Keep everything minimal — later phases add the actual code
- Make sure all TypeScript files will compile with `npx tsc --noEmit`
